# Git commits

When creating or amending commits on behalf of the user:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by:`, `Signed-off-by:` for Cursor, or any AI/IDE co-author line unless the user explicitly asks for it.
- The commit message must contain only what the user requested (Conventional Commits subject/body, etc.).
- Ensure Git hooks are active: `git config core.hooksPath .githooks` once per clone. Hooks strip `Co-authored-by: Cursor` / `cursoragent@cursor.com` before the commit is recorded.
- After every commit, run `git log -1 --format=%B` and confirm no Cursor co-author trailer remains.
- If the environment still injects `Co-authored-by: Cursor` after `git commit`, amend the last commit (only if not pushed) with the same message **without** that trailer, using a message file: `git commit --amend -F /path/to/msg.txt` and verify with `git log -1 --format=%B`.
